violation_description: MAJOR - Observed boba at 77.8-84.6F (3 containers) out on counter since 12pm (~1.5 hrs. prior). Facility allegedly uses TPHC (Time as a Public Health Control), but facility is not tracking time (no temp. logs, no stickers/post it). Employee states boba is used up within an hour and that manager instructed them to throw away any left after 4 hours. Potentially hazardous foods must be cold held at 41F or below, 135F or above, or TPHC can be used with proper labels (start and end time), records and documentation maintained to show food is only held out of temperature control for up to 4 hours and then discarded. Discussed with employee and instructed them to add label with start time = 12pm and discard time = 4pm. Ensure all batches of boba are labeled with start and discard time. Fill out TPHC written procedures within 14 days and keep available on site.

violation_description: MAJOR - Observed boba at 77.8-84.6F (3 containers) out on counter since 12pm (~1.5 hrs. prior). Facility allegedly uses TPHC (Time as a Public Health Control), but facility is not tracking time (no temp. logs, no stickers/post it). Employee states boba is used up within an hour and that manager instructed them to throw away any left after 4 hours. Potentially hazardous foods must be cold held at 41F or below, 135F or above, or TPHC can be used with proper labels (start and end time), records and documentation maintained to show food is only held out of temperature control for up to 4 hours and then discarded. Discussed with employee and instructed them to add label with start time = 12pm and discard time = 4pm. Ensure all batches of boba are labeled with start and discard time. Fill out TPHC written procedures within 14 days and keep available on site.

violation_description:
MAJOR - Observed the following foods at unsafe temperatures:
- chopped tomatoes on ice at 50F, placed there <2hrs prior - moved to cooler
- egg/bacon at 84F - operator states this made ~1hr prior and will discard
- sausage at 65F - operator took out of fridge <30 mins prior for service
- grab n go reach in cooler ~50F in cafe, log shows 40F this morning - PHFs moved to working unit - repair to cold hold at 41F or below
- breakfast burrito measured at 119.3F, sandwich at 131.8F in hot holding unit in cafe - made this morning ~2hrs prior - operator reheated to 165F - hot hold PHFs at 135F or above
- sausage at 59.6F in reach in cooler - repair unit to cold hold <41F; sausage (3) voluntarily discarded
- tofu at 124F, rice at 129F, beans at 125F, in left most hot holding unit made this morning - chef reheated to 165F - repair to hot hold PHFs at >135F
- hummus at 45F, tofu at 45F, pico at 45F, chickpeas (cooked) at 51F, garlic in butter at 46.7F in walk in cooler near chemical closet (ambient 45-46F) - repair to cold hold <41F; move all PHFs to working unit until repaired; 12 qts. chickpeas voluntarily discarded - recommend discarding PHFs in unit since yesterday that are >45F since temperature log shows last temperature taken was 45F yesterday (re-train employees on using temperature logs to ensure 41F or below).
Maintain potentially hazardous foods cold at 41F or below OR hot at 135F or above. Repair coolers to cold hold <41F and hot holding unit to hot hold >135F.

- onion jam (cooked onions, balsamic, sugar) at 74F, made yesterday, on counter - this is considered potentially hazardous unless proven otherwise (Water activity, pH) - keep at 41F or below, 135F or above, or use Time as a Public Health Control - 1/2 quart voluntarily discarded
- burritos at 107-112F, made ~1 hr prior, on shelf - chef reheated to 165F; hot hold at 135F or above
- clam chowder in walk in cooler at 43-44.8F, made yesterday - cold hold at 41F or below; discussed cooling
Maintain potentially hazardous foods at 41F or below OR 135F or above.
